# Phase-6 examples/plugins/ — keep build outputs out of the index;
# whitelist each example's checked-in pre-built artefact.
#
# Each per-language example has its own build outputs that should
# NOT be committed (Rust target/, Node node_modules/, TinyGo
# binaries in the source dir, etc.). The ONE committed artefact per
# example is `pre-built/plugin.wasm` — explicitly whitelisted below.

# Rust
**/target/
**/Cargo.lock
**/*.rs.bk

# Node / pnpm / bun
**/node_modules/
**/dist/
**/.pnpm-store/
**/pnpm-lock.yaml
**/package-lock.json
**/.bun/

# Go
**/go.sum
**/gen/

# C / wit-bindgen-c
**/*.o
**/Makefile.depend

# Generic wasm outputs at the example root — only the curated
# pre-built/plugin.wasm is the committed artefact.
*.wasm
*.cwasm

# Whitelist the canonical checked-in artefact path per example.
# Negation patterns are matched after the includes above, so the
# pre-built/ directory's plugin.wasm survives.
!*/pre-built/
!*/pre-built/plugin.wasm
